     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<span class=\"tex2jax_ignore\"><div class=\"entities\" style=\"line-height: 2.5; direction: ltr\">Tilted State Population of Antimicrobial Peptide \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    PGLa\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " Is Coupled to the Transmembrane Potential<br>Cationic antimicrobial peptide \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    PGLa\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " gets into close contact with the anionic bacterial cell membrane, facilitating cross-membrane transport phenomena and membrane disruption depending on the concentration. The mechanisms of action are closely associated with the tilted insertion geometry of \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    PGLa\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       ". Therefore, we aimed to understand the interaction between the transmembrane potential (TMP) and the orientation of the membrane-bound \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    PGLa\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " helix. Molecular dynamics simulations were performed with TMP, and we found that the \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    PGLa\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " tilt angle relative to the membrane is coupled with the TMP. Elevated TMP increases the population of the tilted state. We observed positive feedback between the tilt angle and the TMP, which occurs due to the electrostatic interaction between the peptidic helix and the \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    Na+\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " cations at the membrane–\n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    water\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " interface. These TMP coupled phenomena can contribute to understanding the direct antimicrobial and adjuvant effects of \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    PGLa\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " in combination with regular antibiotics.</div></span>"
