    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<span class=\"tex2jax_ignore\"><div class=\"entities\" style=\"line-height: 2.5; direction: ltr\">Interaction of the inhibitory peptides \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    ShK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " and \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    HmK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " with the voltage-gated potassium channel \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KV1.3\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       ": Role of conformational dynamics<br>ABSTRACT: Peptide toxins that adopt the \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    ShK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " fold can inhibit the voltage-gated potassium channel \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KV1.3\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " with IC50 values in the pM range, and are therefore potential leads for drugs targeting autoimmune and neuroinflammatory diseases. NMR relaxation measurements and pressure-dependent NMR have shown that, despite being cross-linked by disulfide bonds, \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    ShK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " itself is flexible in solution. This flexibility affects the local structure around the pharmacophore for \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KV1.3\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " channel blockade and, in particular, the relative orientation of the key Lys and Tyr side chains (Lys22 and Tyr23 in \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    ShK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       "), and has implications for the design of \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KV1.3\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " inhibitors. In this study, we have performed molecular dynamics (MD) simulations on \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    ShK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " and a close homolog, \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    HmK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       ", in order to probe the conformational space occupied by the Lys and Tyr residues, and docked the different conformations with a recently determined cryo-EM structure of the \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KV1.3\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " channel. Although \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    ShK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " and \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    HmK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " have 60% sequence identity, their dynamic behaviors are quite different, with \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    ShK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " sampling a broad range of conformations over the course of a \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #baffc9; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    5 μs\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">STIME</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " MD simulation, while \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    HmK\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " is relatively rigid. We also investigated the importance of conformational dynamics, in particular the distance between the side chains of the key dyad Lys22 and Tyr23, for binding to \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KV1.3\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       ". Although these peptides have quite different dynamics, the dyad in both adopts a similar configuration upon binding, revealing a conformational selection upon binding to \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
