       "<span class=\"tex2jax_ignore\"><div class=\"entities\" style=\"line-height: 2.5; direction: ltr\">Assessing the Activation of \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    Tyrosine Kinase\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KIT\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " through Free Energy Calculations<br>\n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KIT\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " is a type 3 receptor \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    tyrosine kinase\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " that plays a crucial role in cellular growth and proliferation. Mutations in \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KIT\n",
       "    <span style=\"font-size: 0.8em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.5rem\">MOL</span>\n",
       "</mark>\n",
       " can dysregulate its active–inactive equilibrium. Activating mutations drive cancer growth, while deactivating mutations result in the loss of skin and hair pigmentation in a disease known as piebaldism. Here, we propose a method based on molecular dynamics and free energy calculations to predict the functional effect of \n",
       "<mark class=\"entity\" style=\"background: #bae1ff; padding: 0.45em 0.6em; margin: 0 0.25em; line-height: 1; border-radius: 0.35em;\">\n",
       "    KIT\n",
